title: Sins (Starker)
body:
Peter had been ready.  He’d been completely prepared to relinquish all of his sinful thoughts.  Homosexuality was wrong.  Of course he knew that, he’d heard it every day of his life growing up.  Men do not lie with other men.  It’s a sin. So when he realised that he had these… feelings for men, he tried to push the feelings away – to bury them.  But he just couldn’t.  

Which is why Peter found himself sitting on a chair in a circle of men and women of all ages, all of which shared one common goal – to stop being gay.  The man who ran the session was world-renowned for his homosexual aversion therapy.  Dr. Tony Stark.  Peter had heard great things about him, and he’d done all of his research before attending the session.  So many positive reviews.  So many successful stories.  Peter would be cured of his disease, he was sure of it.

That was, until Dr. Stark entered the room and Peter suddenly felt a fluttering sensation in his lower abdomen, like nothing else he’d ever felt before.  Stark’s photographs on the website didn’t do him justice – this man was tall, muscular, insanely handsome, and there was just… something… about him that made Peter go weak at the knees.  

This wasn’t good.  This wasn’t good at all.  He’d come to this session to be cured of his toxic thoughts and all he could think about was how good it would feel to have Stark’s hands all over his naked body.  Stark opened his mouth to speak, and his voice was low, husky, the sexiest thing Peter had ever heard.

He stared at the older man, overwhelmed.  He’d never felt such intense things about someone he’d only just met.  It was weird, and it was completely wrong in every conceivable way, but Peter just couldn’t look away.  He couldn’t bring himself to stand up and leave.  He didn’t even care that his thoughts were against everything he was raised to believe.  All he knew was that he wanted Dr. Stark, and he wanted him bad.

He felt someone nudge him from the right, and he was broken out of his disturbing thoughts and brought back to reality.  He glanced around and noticed everyone in the group was staring at him.  He felt his cheeks grow hot, and then looked back at Dr. Stark, who was also staring at him, eyebrows raised.

Peter swallowed.  “I- I’m sorry?” he said, wishing he could disappear.  He hoped nobody had noticed how he’d been staring so… so hungrily at the man in front of him.

“I asked your name,” Dr. Stark prompted, smiling a little. Peter’s heart skipped a beat at the way he had smiled at him.

“I’m Peter,” he said quickly, staring up at Dr. Stark intently – wanting him to know who he was.  “I’m Peter Parker.”

“Tony Stark,” Dr. Stark said warmly, reaching a hand out to shake Peter’s.  “It’s very nice to meet you, and to start you on your journey to recovery.”  Peter nodded, shaking Stark’s hand and trying not to think about how good it felt to touch him.

But moments later, Stark had let go of his hand and moved onto the boy next to him.

Peter knew that Stark wasn’t starting him on his journey to recovery – more like he was leading him down a one-way street to hell. But somehow, Peter didn’t mind.

summary: Stephen Strange laying in a leather couch, talking to a therapist: And then my cloak smacked his ass! God, can you imagine how I...
body:
Stephen Strange laying in a leather couch, talking to a therapist: And then my cloak smacked his ass! God, can you imagine how I felt when he turned around?


Therapist: it’s perfectly normal to feel bashful and embarrassed-


Strange, sitting up: No, I felt hot- the only embarrassing part was Dr. Banner sticking around because he was too anxious and shy to speak up while Tony and I stared into each other’s eyes.


Therapist: I think we’re done for the day Doctor.
